      "question": "What is the definition of 'lecturer' in the university policy?",
      "answer": "According to section 25.1, a lecturer is defined as a faculty member who teaches courses on a regular or permanent basis, with a teaching load of over 30 hours per week within office hours, or during weekends. Additionally, administrative personnel engaged in part-time teaching are also considered lecturers."
